title: X Factor Celebrity song list announced - and Jenny makes 'dig' at the judges
text:
Get the biggest celebs stories by email Subscribe Thank you for subscribing We have more newsletters Show me See our privacy notice Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email

The song list for the first X Factor: Celebrity live show has been announced.

There will be 13 acts competing to impress the judges and win that sensational record contract.

And there have been some major changes since the auditions - with The Islanders, who have changed their name to No Love Lost, singing an original song

While The Chase star Jenny Ryan has appeared to have made a sly dig at the judges with her song choice.

Here is the full song list for the first X Factor : Celebrity live show.

(Image: ITV)

(Image: ITV)

GROUPS

Try Star – Medley ‘Pony’ Ginuwine / ‘Old Town Road’ NAS X.

V5- Medley ‘Bad Guy’ Billie Eilish / ‘Taki Taki’ DJ Snake.

Max and Harvey – ‘When will I be famous’ BROS.

No Love Lost – ‘All or Nothing’ original song.

(Image: ITV)

OVERS

Ricki Lake- ‘Landslide’ Fleetwood Mac.

Jenny Ryan – ‘Rise like a phoenix’ Conchita Wurst.

Victoria Ekanoye – ‘Never tear us apart’ INXS.

Vinnie Jones – ‘Everybody needs somebody’ The Blues Brothers.

Martin Bashir - “Danke schoen’ Wayne Newton.

(Image: ITV)

UNDERS

Megan McKenna – ‘This’ original song.

Olivia Olson – ‘Anyone who had a heart’ Dionne Warwick.

Jonny Labey – ‘Show me love’ Robin S.

Kevin McHale – ‘Good as hell’ Lizzo.

(Image: ITV)

Jenny was initially dumped out of the competition by Nicole Scherzinger - but the controversial decision was slammed by the public.

After some consultation, the judges opted to give Jenny a place in the live shows following her incredible rendition of Queen's Somebody to Love.

Giving her reaction to being invited back, Jenny said: "I've loved every moment of the X Factor and I'm delighted to be able to get the opportunity to perform live.

"The response from the public has been amazing - what an incredible experience. I'm so pleased it's continuing!"

(Image: ITV)

Jenny's mentor, former Pussycat Doll Nicole, added: "Jenny was just brilliant at her audition in LA. That voice of hers is one of a kind, and she's an amazing person to get to know.

"So it was such a tough decision to make. After a lot of discussion we all agreed we had to put her through

"The Overs are gonna smash it this year!"

(Image: ITV)

While Vinnie Jones will sing some of wife Tanya’s favourite songs as a tribute to her.

Vinnie told the Mirror: "There’s one song that I like, which I might be singing. It’s one that means a lot to us. I can see her now looking out the window of the car tapping along to it. There are a lot of songs that mean a lot to us.

"I’m not treating it like a singing competition, I’m doing it as a tribute for Tanya."

(Image: Getty)

He added: “I’ve got a song that I could get emotional to, but Tanya wouldn’t want me to crack up. It’s a ballad, an Irish song, it’s basically about me and her. So it’s a sad song.

"If I can get through that, I think that could bring the house down.

"The biggest part of doing X Factor was Tanya. She loved the show, she thought it would be brilliant. I’m like, ‘No no, really?’ She was like ‘yeah you’ll be brilliant, I love it,’ then my daughter jumped in, Kaley, and she’s like you’ve got to do it.

"It gave Tanya something to look forward to, to come over to London and get well for.

"Sadly it was a bridge too far for her."

*X Factor: Celebrity airs tonight on ITV at 8.20pm
description: The Islanders have changed their name and are singing an original song for the first Celebrity X Factor live show
